1 Introduction
The reaction network for maleic anhydride (MA) hydrogenation is shown in Fig. 1. [13]. In this process, both hydrogenation and hydrogenolysis reactions are involved. Some of the reaction products, succinic anhydride (SA), γ-butyrolactone (GBL), tetrahydrofurane (THF), and 1,4-butanediol (BDO), are valuable products that find a wide market as solvents or as starting material for polymers like polyuretanes. In particular, SA is required as intermediate for the chemical, pharmaceutical and food industries [1].
