3.2.4 Effect of Weighted Hourly Space Velocity (WHSV)
The hydrogenation of maleic anhydride was carried out at 140 C with WHSV varying from 0.2 to 3 h1 (Fig. 6). It was seen that as the WHSV increased, the conversion of maleic anhydride decreased. And as the WHSV increased, the yield of SA fell exponentially. The conversion decreased from 100% at 2 h1 to 81% at 3h1, and the selectivity of SA fell from 97 to 62% during this period. A high SA selectivity and MA conversion could be obtained at WHSV of 2 h1.
